cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.SI 

The paper discusses bibliometric evaluation of scientific publications, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is the most likely category as it deals with the organization, retrieval, and evaluation of digital information. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also likely as it deals with the analysis and retrieval of information from large datasets. cs.CY (Computers and Society) is relevant as the paper discusses the evaluation of research organizations. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) are less likely but still possible as they deal with the evaluation of security systems and social networks, respectively.
